casebody.data:
Thomas James DUNLAP, Plaintiff-Appellant,
v.
AIG, INC., Commerce and Industry Insurance Company and AIG Domestic Claims, Inc. Corporations, Defendants-Appellees. No. 17-1503 Court of Appeals of Iowa. Filed January 9, 2019

Thomas Dunlap appeals the dismissal of his civil suit against his former employer's workers' compensation insurance carrier following the district court's grant of summary judgment in the insurers' favor. AFFIRMED IN PART, REVERSED IN PART, AND REMANDED FOR FURTHER PROCEEDINGS.

DECISION WITHOUT PUBLISHED OPINION See Iowa R. App. P. 6.904

AFFIRMED IN PART, REVERSED IN PART. REMANDED FOR FURTHER PROCEEDINGS.
